<title>SRI LANKA: Merchant Bank up six pct on retail buying.</title>
<headline>Merchant Bank up six pct on retail buying.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Buying by small investors pushed up Merchant Bank of Sri Lanka Ltd by six percent, or 1.25 rupees to 22.25 rupees, on 3,300 shares, brokers said.</p>
<p>&quot;Merchant Bank is cheap and fairly liquid, which makes it an ideal retail stock,&quot; a local broker said.</p>
<p>Investors were also bullish on the share because the company had a large exposure to the high-performing plantation sector, after having underwritten three of the six tea firms now trading in the market, he said.</p>
<p>--Colombo newsroom (941) 434319</p>
